This paper is primarily focused on the security of password-based authentication means, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of attack methods and the need for better proactive password checkers and recovery tools, which could also be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), cybercrime (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and software engineering (cs.SE).
